"adj. 惊骇的，吓呆的 【英】 adj. 惊骇的，吓呆的(feel ing great horror or dismay; terrified) 【记】 a+ghast(=ghost鬼, 害怕)→害怕的，吓呆 的 adj. 惊骇的, 吓呆的(被惊讶、恐怖或惊异侵袭的) = terrified 【例】I stood aghast at this unforeseen disaster 我被这意外的灾祸吓呆了. 【源】源自ghost n 鬼, 幽灵 【记】a + ghost 鬼→见鬼了→惊骇 【相关】gast 使惊讶 aghast (adj.)  c.1300, agast, ""terrified,"" past participle of Middle English agasten ""to frighten"" (c.1200), from a- intensive prefix + Old English gæstan ""to terrify,"" from gæst ""spirit, ghost"" (see ghost). The -gh- spelling appeared early 15c. in Scottish and is possibly a Flemish influence, or after ghost, etc. It became general after 1700."
